<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>There are several bike accessories you can invest in to help you commute safely and comfortably by bike. A bike lock should be second only to your helmet.  </p>

<p>There are plenty of bike lock styles to choose from but hundreds of Amazon shoppers agree that the SPGOOD chain lock offers impressive protection, describing it as a 'super, really solid, heavy chain' and 'great quality bike lock'.</p>

<p>With over 1,000 ratings on Amazon, the SPGOOD Bike Lock is a smart choice for those who want peace of mind when leaving their bike unattended. Even better, the lock is now 50 per cent off on Amazon meaning you can pick it up for only £11.04.</p>

<p>The SPGOOD Bike lock is Amazon's Choice for 'Cycling Locks' and boasts a near-perfect average score of 4.6 out of 5</p>

<p>With a near-perfect average score of 4.6 out of 5 on Amazon, the SPGOOD Bike Lock is a popular and highly-rated bike lock. If you want extra security when posting up at work, school, the gym or coffee shop- this is sure to put you at ease.  </p>

<p>At well under £20, it's a real bargain that despite its low price tag comes up superior in terms of security. As a rule of thumb the heavier the chain, the harder it is to cut so at 750g it's enough to deter thieves, plus it's light enough to carry in your bag. </p>

<p>The SPGOOD Bike Lock has received a lot of respect from cyclists thanks to the seven millimetres thick hardened steel and durable, cut-resistant design. At 83 centimetres long, it's enough to wrap around the wheels and frame of the bike- giving you extra peace of mind. </p>

<p>Designed with a canvas sleeve, it will not only stymie a hacksaw but will protect the chain from scratching your bike too. Win-win. </p>

<p>The D-lock versus chain lock is a hotly debated topic, but many shoppers have commented on how the SPGOOD chain lock gives you more options of where to lock your bike, not to mention it's easier to transport. </p>

<p>'This bike lock is so hassle free compared to my previous D-lock. No need to carry key as this is a combination lock and this is a five numbered combination secure lock. Compared to D-lock, this is flexible when coming to locking to no standard objects and very easy to carry.' </p>

<p>SPGOOD bicycle lock uses a five-digit combination code, so you don't have to worry about losing your key </p>

<p>While some of the reviews have stated that the SPGOOD is slightly heavier than some other locks, many added that this is reassuring. </p>

<p>'This is the most sturdy bike lock I've ever seen. It's heavy but that's is because your bike is super safe. It collapses small so it's easy to carry with you on a bike ride but parking your bike up you know that it's completely safe. Can be used for other things but for the bike it gives me complete peace of mind. Simple to set up and super safe.'</p>

<p>The locks simplicity makes it a big winner with shoppers, with another writing: 'This a great bicycle chain, long enough to put it around my bike and very strong which is the reason why cutting is almost impossible. It's very convenient without having to use a key to lock it. It was easy to use or reset code and there are instructions on setting up the combination lock which was also helpful.' </p>

<p>A third raved: 'Bought this as an easy to carry lock for stopping at the local shops etc. Long enough to fit round both wheels and frame, and a hoop etc. Fast to set 4 numbers and you're off, no faffing with a key etc. Exactly what I wanted.'</p>

